node.text:
With a preference for classic designs, free-form shapes, and a neutral color palette, vintage collector Maggie Holladay (@claudehome) was drawn to @maidenhome’s Spring 2021 Collection for her New York studio. With a focus on the inherent beauty of natural materials, the items are meant to age masterfully over time and are crafted to look—and feel—like works of art. 

See how Maggie styles the pieces in her East Village artist's loft here: https://bit.ly/3tELSy7

node.text:
Actor Adrian Grenier (@adriangrenier) wanted his mother, Karesse, to live a little closer to him. “I made a deal with her,” he said. “If I could make you a nice house, maybe you’ll consider having a shorter commute so I can see you more often.”

Together with designer Estelle Bailey-Babenzien (@thedreamawake), the two designed a Brooklyn Brownstone parlor-level duplex with Adrian’s mother’s values in mind. Rich metals, natural woods, reflective surfaces and sustainable elements, like a solar thermal system and recycled denim insulation, all folded into the look of the home. 

“My mom is a light in my life. I wanted to give that back to her.” Copy this link to see the full story: https://bit.ly/3q8JXjq

Video by @quinnebago, design by @thedreamawake, styling by @dyphornewyork

node.title: Inside Adrian Grenier’s Brooklyn Brownstone Renovation for His Mother

node.text: “It was the size that blew us away,” says Julia Rouzaud of her 3,200-square-foot house, located just 20 minutes outside of Paris. More rare, perhaps, is the structure’s design: Built in the 19th century and expanded in the 1950s, it merges two eras that don’t typically collide. We visit the @goodmoods founder and family at their reimagined home at the link in bio. Photo and styling by @amandine__jules, story by @lydiageisel

node.text: From the swirling S-shaped bookshelf to the yellow-painted built-in sofa, every detail in @annapolons and @fefoeats’s living room was meticulously chosen. We visit more of their lovingly renovated Brooklyn brownstone at the link in bio. Photos by @nicole_franzen, styling by @kateberryberry

node.text: Books, bowls, plants, candles—just choosing what to put on your coffee table can be overwhelming. We can help with that! Our style editor @juliastevens_ has an easy (un)styling trick to make crafting your tabletop display easy and, bonus, it will help you read more (we love @leannefordinteriors’s version pictured above.)
